  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Let his posterity be cut off,.... As the seed of the wicked are said to be, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 37:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or cut down, as a tree to the very root; as the Jewish nation was by the axe of God's judgment, which, John says, was laid to the root of the tree, and the blow just going to be given, as it was in a few years after, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 3:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " or, as the Targum, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"let his end be for destruction;'' ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and so the Syriac version, \"let their end be for destruction\"; their last end, which it is said shall be cut off, and issue in death, eternal death; when the end of a good man is peace and eternal life, see Psalm 37:37. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and so the Syriac version, \"let their end be for destruction\"; their last end, which it is said shall be cut off, and issue in death, eternal death; when the end of a good man is peace and eternal life, see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 37:37",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And in the generation following let their name be blotted out: or, in another age (d); the next age, the third generation; meaning the name of the posterity of Judas, and the name of the people of the Jews, so as to be spoken of with honour and reputation; but, instead of that, they are for a taunt, a proverb, and a curse, in all places. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(d)  \"in generatione altera\", Pagninus, Montanus, &c. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(d)  \"in generatione altera\", Pagninus, Montanus, &c. ",
