      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 37:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". With reference to ימּח instead of ימּח (contracted from ימּחה), vid., Ges. 75, rem. 8. A Jewish acrostic interpretation of the name ישׁוּ runs: ימּח שׁמו וזכרו. This curse shall overtake the family of the υἱὸς τῆς ἀπωλείας. All the sins of his parents and ancestors shall remain indelible above before God the Judge, and here below the race, equally guilty, shall be rooted out even to its memory, i.e., to the last trace of it. ",
        "children": []
      }
